<TITLE> DV applicants to pay fees before interview </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 17 (bdnews24.com)  All US Diversity Visa applicants, will have to deposit their visa fees at Standard Chartered Bank's North Gulshan branch prior to their interview from May 23. A statement from the American embassy made the announcement on Sunday. The statement said that from May 23, the embassy's Consular Section will no longer accept DV application fees on the scheduled date of interview. Instead, the applicant will have to deposit fees at Standard Chartered Bank's North Gulshan branch at 189 Gulshan Avenue (North), Gulshan-2, Dhaka-1212 prior to their interviews. The applicant will have to show the Standard Chartered Bank issued DV receipt during interview. Visa fees can be deposited between 10am  4pm from Sundays  Thursdays. The statement also points out that the deposited fee is non-refundable. The notice also states that the deposit of fees is not related with travel dates and all applicants appearing for the interview will have to pay the fee even if they plan to travel la
